text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Discrimination against Southern Drawl%0a:Author: MitulS%0a:Section: F%0a:Completed: 23.04.2021 - 21:28%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210512-124321-726220#%0a* [-12.05.2021 - 05:43-] || TA_mason marked as complete%0a#foxend 210512-124321-726220#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe media at large propagates discrimination against southern American accents.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aVideo link: https://www.facebook.com/traecrowder/videos/708932246265481/%0a%0aSouthern drawl is a dialectic feature of southern American accents that features vowel diphthongization of front vowels in particular. More generally, stressed vowels are extended, unstressed vowels are shortened, and the tongue backness is greater when enunciating vowels.%0a%0aAlthough discrimination has long existed between Northern and Southern accents in both directions, it has moved much further against Southern drawl as urban areas steadily converged to a standard much closer to Northern accents.%0a%0aOne thing I found interesting in the video is that Southern accents are so heavily discriminated against today that they have become culturally synonymous with stupidity and lack of education in popular media. Even as American culture becomes more accepting of linguistic diversity in modern times, this trend seems to not be slowing down at a comparable rate.%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_mason:)
