diff:1619238529:1619238529:=1,51d0%0a%3c :Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a%3c :Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a%3c :Title: Discrimination against Southern Drawl%0a%3c :Author: MitulS%0a%3c :Section: F%0a%3c :Completed: 23.04.2021 - 21:28%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c Summary: \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c The media at large propagates discrimination against southern American accents.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Video link: https://www.facebook.com/traecrowder/videos/708932246265481/%0a%3c %0a%3c Southern drawl is a dialectic feature of southern American accents that features vowel diphthongization of front vowels in particular. More generally, stressed vowels are extended, unstressed vowels are shortened, and the tongue backness is greater when enunciating vowels.%0a%3c %0a%3c Although discrimination has long existed between Northern and Southern accents in both directions, it has moved much further against Southern drawl as urban areas steadily converged to a standard much closer to Northern accents.%0a%3c %0a%3c One thing I found interesting in the video is that Southern accents are so heavily discriminated against today that they have become culturally synonymous with stupidity and lack of education in popular media. Even as American culture becomes more accepting of linguistic diversity in modern times, this trend seems to not be slowing down at a comparable rate.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
